Package planeair.graph.graphutil

Class Automation

java.lang.Object
planeair.graph.graphutil.Automation
public abstract class Automation extends Object
Automates every step of the Coloring Challenge where we have to import 20 graphs, color them and store the results.
Author:
Nathan LIEGEON

    • importDataFromFolder

      public static TreeSet<TestGraph> importDataFromFolder(String path, String[] identifiers, char placeholder, ExecutorService threadPool)

      Parameters:

      identifiers - the strings the name will be compared to
      placeholder - character that should be replaced by numbers for the check

      Returns:
      the list of Graphs that were imported ordered by ID

    • isFileLike

      public static boolean isFileLike(String filename, String[] identifiers, char placeholder)
      Tells whether or not a file is of a similar form to one of the identifiers ex : identifier is "testGraphX.txt" filename is "testGraph12.txt", placeholder is 'X' The function will return true for the example This function is also case sensitive
      Parameters:
      filename - name your are testing
      identifiers - array containing different identifiers the filename will be compared to
      placeholder - character which should be replaced by numbers
      Returns:
      boolean telling whether the file was similar to one of the identifiers or not
